"{\"uid\": \"theatlantic.com-international-archive-2024-05-geopolitics-doping-wada-olympics-678409\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"The agency charged with keeping sports doping-free now seems vulnerable to manipulation by malign states.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 105, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The agency\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 10}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 32, \"to\": 38}, {\"ngram\": \"manipulation\", \"from\": 75, \"to\": 87}, {\"ngram\": \"malign states\", \"from\": 91, \"to\": 104}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2021, on the eve of the Tokyo Olympics, 23 top Chinese swimmers tested positive for the drug trimetazidine.\", \"from\": 107, \"to\": 217, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 157, \"end\": 164, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999999994251993, \"rank\": 5.749223433152553e-10, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the eve\", \"from\": 119, \"to\": 126}, {\"ngram\": \"the Tokyo Olympics\", \"from\": 130, \"to\": 148}, {\"ngram\": \"the drug trimetazidine\", \"from\": 194, \"to\": 216}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In its proper clinical setting, the medication is used to treat angina.\", \"from\": 218, \"to\": 289, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its proper clinical setting\", \"from\": 221, \"to\": 248}, {\"ngram\": \"the medication\", \"from\": 250, \"to\": 264}, {\"ngram\": \"angina\", \"from\": 282, \"to\": 288}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But for an athlete or a coach willing to cheat, it is a performance-enhancing drug, boosting the heart muscle's functioning.\", \"from\": 290, \"to\": 414, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an athlete\", \"from\": 298, \"to\": 308}, {\"ngram\": \"a coach\", \"from\": 312, \"to\": 319}, {\"ngram\": \"a performance-enhancing drug\", \"from\": 344, \"to\": 372}, {\"ngram\": \"the heart muscle's functioning\", \"from\": 383, \"to\": 413}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nonprescription use of trimetazidine, or TMZ, is prohibited at all times, not just during competition; the default sanction for an athlete's violation is a four-year ban.\", \"from\": 415, \"to\": 585, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Nonprescription use\", \"from\": 415, \"to\": 434}, {\"ngram\": \"trimetazidine\", \"from\": 438, \"to\": 451}, {\"ngram\": \"TMZ\", \"from\": 456, \"to\": 459}, {\"ngram\": \"all times\", \"from\": 478, \"to\": 487}, {\"ngram\": \"competition\", \"from\": 505, \"to\": 516}, {\"ngram\": \"the default sanction\", \"from\": 518, \"to\": 538}, {\"ngram\": \"an athlete's violation\", \"from\": 543, \"to\": 565}, {\"ngram\": \"a four-year ban\", \"from\": 569, \"to\": 584}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The testing that ensnared so many members of China's swim team was conducted under the auspices of the national anti-doping agency, known as CHINADA.\", \"from\": 587, \"to\": 736, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 632, \"end\": 637, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999999275232794, \"rank\": 7.212074791054842e-08, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The testing\", \"from\": 587, \"to\": 598}, {\"ngram\": \"so many members\", \"from\": 613, \"to\": 628}, {\"ngram\": \"the auspices\", \"from\": 670, \"to\": 682}, {\"ngram\": \"the national anti-doping agency\", \"from\": 686, \"to\": 717}, {\"ngram\": \"CHINADA\", \"from\": 728, \"to\": 735}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Each country in international competition has its own such agency-America's is USADA, which I serve-and they all operate under the umbrella of the World Anti-Doping Agency.\", \"from\": 737, \"to\": 909, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 816, \"end\": 821, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USADA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Each country\", \"from\": 737, \"to\": 749}, {\"ngram\": \"international competition\", \"from\": 753, \"to\": 778}, {\"ngram\": \"its own such agency\", \"from\": 783, \"to\": 802}, {\"ngram\": \"America\", \"from\": 803, \"to\": 810}, {\"ngram\": \"the umbrella\", \"from\": 864, \"to\": 876}, {\"ngram\": \"the World Anti-Doping Agency\", \"from\": 880, \"to\": 908}]}, {\"sentence\": \"WADA is the ultimate authority, responsible for ensuring that national agencies enforce the rules.\", \"from\": 910, \"to\": 1008, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 910, \"to\": 914}, {\"ngram\": \"the ultimate authority\", \"from\": 918, \"to\": 940}, {\"ngram\": \"national agencies\", \"from\": 972, \"to\": 989}, {\"ngram\": \"the rules\", \"from\": 998, \"to\": 1007}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yet shortly before the 2021 Games got under way, CHINADAvacated the 23 violations, giving a cock-and-bull story about accidental contamination in the kitchen where the athletes' meals were prepared.\", \"from\": 1009, \"to\": 1207, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 2021 Games\", \"from\": 1028, \"to\": 1042}, {\"ngram\": \"way\", \"from\": 1053, \"to\": 1056}, {\"ngram\": \"the 23 violations\", \"from\": 1073, \"to\": 1090}, {\"ngram\": \"a cock-and-bull story\", \"from\": 1099, \"to\": 1120}, {\"ngram\": \"accidental contamination\", \"from\": 1127, \"to\": 1151}, {\"ngram\": \"the kitchen\", \"from\": 1155, \"to\": 1166}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes' meals\", \"from\": 1173, \"to\": 1192}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And WADA simply accepted CHINADA's obviously suspect ruling.\", \"from\": 1208, \"to\": 1268, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 1212, \"to\": 1216}, {\"ngram\": \"CHINADA's obviously suspect ruling\", \"from\": 1233, \"to\": 1267}]}, {\"sentence\": \"WADA failed even to publish its decision.\", \"from\": 1270, \"to\": 1311, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 1270, \"to\": 1274}, {\"ngram\": \"its decision\", \"from\": 1298, \"to\": 1310}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The worldwas alerted only last monthby whistleblowers who pushed evidence of the scandal to the media.\", \"from\": 1312, \"to\": 1414, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The worldwas\", \"from\": 1312, \"to\": 1324}, {\"ngram\": \"only last monthby whistleblowers\", \"from\": 1333, \"to\": 1365}, {\"ngram\": \"evidence\", \"from\": 1377, \"to\": 1385}, {\"ngram\": \"the scandal\", \"from\": 1389, \"to\": 1400}, {\"ngram\": \"the media\", \"from\": 1404, \"to\": 1413}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Prompted by the revelations to respond, WADAissued a statementciting its prior conclusion \\\"that it was not in a position to disprove the possibility that contamination was the source of TMZ\\\" and \\\"that, given the specific circumstances of the asserted contamination, the athletes would be held to have no fault or negligence.\\\"\", \"from\": 1415, \"to\": 1740, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the revelations\", \"from\": 1427, \"to\": 1442}, {\"ngram\": \"its prior conclusion\", \"from\": 1484, \"to\": 1504}, {\"ngram\": \"a position\", \"from\": 1525, \"to\": 1535}, {\"ngram\": \"the possibility\", \"from\": 1548, \"to\": 1563}, {\"ngram\": \"contamination\", \"from\": 1569, \"to\": 1582}, {\"ngram\": \"the source\", \"from\": 1587, \"to\": 1597}, {\"ngram\": \"TMZ\", \"from\": 1601, \"to\": 1604}, {\"ngram\": \"the specific circumstances\", \"from\": 1623, \"to\": 1649}, {\"ngram\": \"the asserted contamination\", \"from\": 1653, \"to\": 1679}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 1681, \"to\": 1693}, {\"ngram\": \"no fault\", \"from\": 1716, \"to\": 1724}, {\"ngram\": \"negligence\", \"from\": 1728, \"to\": 1738}]}, {\"sentence\": \"WADA's failure of oversight and lack of transparency are corroding fair competition-and that has come to haunt clean athletes around the world.\", \"from\": 1742, \"to\": 1885, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"WADA's failure\", \"from\": 1742, \"to\": 1756}, {\"ngram\": \"oversight\", \"from\": 1760, \"to\": 1769}, {\"ngram\": \"lack\", \"from\": 1774, \"to\": 1778}, {\"ngram\": \"transparency\", \"from\": 1782, \"to\": 1794}, {\"ngram\": \"fair competition\", \"from\": 1809, \"to\": 1825}, {\"ngram\": \"clean athletes\", \"from\": 1853, \"to\": 1867}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1875, \"to\": 1884}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If WADA had properly upheld its mission, China would likely have lost 13 of its top swimmers chosen for the Olympic team at Tokyo.\", \"from\": 1886, \"to\": 2016, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1927, \"end\": 1932, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999999275232794, \"rank\": 7.212074791054842e-08, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 2010, \"end\": 2015, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6365883364821878e-18, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 1889, \"to\": 1893}, {\"ngram\": \"its mission\", \"from\": 1914, \"to\": 1925}, {\"ngram\": \"its top swimmers\", \"from\": 1962, \"to\": 1978}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic team\", \"from\": 1990, \"to\": 2006}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, Chinawon six medals, three of them gold, in the pool.\", \"from\": 2017, \"to\": 2079, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Instead, Chinawon six medals\", \"from\": 2017, \"to\": 2045}, {\"ngram\": \"the pool\", \"from\": 2070, \"to\": 2078}]}, {\"sentence\": \"USADA has the job of ensuring that American swimmers abide by the rules and compete clean; as a result of WADA's inaction, several of them potentially lost podium places in Tokyo that they deserved.\", \"from\": 2081, \"to\": 2279, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2081, \"end\": 2086, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USADA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}, {\"begin\": 2116, \"end\": 2124, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.455422135538356e-25, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2254, \"end\": 2259, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6365883364821878e-18, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the job\", \"from\": 2091, \"to\": 2098}, {\"ngram\": \"the rules\", \"from\": 2143, \"to\": 2152}, {\"ngram\": \"a result\", \"from\": 2175, \"to\": 2183}, {\"ngram\": \"WADA's inaction\", \"from\": 2187, \"to\": 2202}, {\"ngram\": \"podium places\", \"from\": 2237, \"to\": 2250}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Worse, the world body's enforcement failures have made national anti-doping agencies such as CHINADA hostage to bad regimes, turning the agencies and the athletes they oversee into pawns in a cynical geopolitical game of prestige and power.\", \"from\": 2280, \"to\": 2520, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the world body's enforcement failures\", \"from\": 2287, \"to\": 2324}, {\"ngram\": \"national anti-doping agencies\", \"from\": 2335, \"to\": 2364}, {\"ngram\": \"CHINADA hostage\", \"from\": 2373, \"to\": 2388}, {\"ngram\": \"bad regimes\", \"from\": 2392, \"to\": 2403}, {\"ngram\": \"the agencies\", \"from\": 2413, \"to\": 2425}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 2430, \"to\": 2442}, {\"ngram\": \"pawns\", \"from\": 2461, \"to\": 2466}, {\"ngram\": \"a cynical geopolitical game\", \"from\": 2470, \"to\": 2497}, {\"ngram\": \"prestige\", \"from\": 2501, \"to\": 2509}, {\"ngram\": \"power\", \"from\": 2514, \"to\": 2519}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What we are seeing is a reinvention of the bad old days of the Cold War, when East Germany tried fraudulently to demonstrate the superiority of state socialism bysystematically dopingits athletes.\", \"from\": 2522, \"to\": 2718, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2600, \"end\": 2612, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/East_Germany\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.556018545611266e-21, \"text\": \"East Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/East_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/East_Germany\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a reinvention\", \"from\": 2544, \"to\": 2557}, {\"ngram\": \"the bad old days\", \"from\": 2561, \"to\": 2577}, {\"ngram\": \"the Cold War\", \"from\": 2581, \"to\": 2593}, {\"ngram\": \"the superiority\", \"from\": 2647, \"to\": 2662}, {\"ngram\": \"state socialism\", \"from\": 2666, \"to\": 2681}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 2709, \"to\": 2717}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Back then, no international anti-doping movement existed, and East Germany's cheating went suspected but largely undetected until years later.\", \"from\": 2719, \"to\": 2861, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2781, \"end\": 2793, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/East_Germany\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.556018545611266e-21, \"text\": \"East Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/East_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/East_Germany\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no international anti-doping movement\", \"from\": 2730, \"to\": 2767}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By then, it was too late for justice; the harms done-both to the athletes' health and to the credibility of the competition in that era-were permanent.\", \"from\": 2862, \"to\": 3013, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"justice\", \"from\": 2891, \"to\": 2898}, {\"ngram\": \"the harms\", \"from\": 2900, \"to\": 2909}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes' health\", \"from\": 2923, \"to\": 2943}, {\"ngram\": \"the credibility\", \"from\": 2951, \"to\": 2966}, {\"ngram\": \"the competition\", \"from\": 2970, \"to\": 2985}, {\"ngram\": \"that era\", \"from\": 2989, \"to\": 2997}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Today, we have the World Anti-Doping Agency to police international sports-but enforcement works only if the watchdog itself is unbiased, conflict-free, and effective.\", \"from\": 3014, \"to\": 3181, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the World Anti-Doping Agency\", \"from\": 3029, \"to\": 3057}, {\"ngram\": \"the watchdog\", \"from\": 3119, \"to\": 3131}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the Paris Games this summer, clean competition is very much in doubt.\", \"from\": 3182, \"to\": 3254, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Paris Games\", \"from\": 3185, \"to\": 3200}, {\"ngram\": \"clean competition\", \"from\": 3214, \"to\": 3231}, {\"ngram\": \"doubt\", \"from\": 3248, \"to\": 3253}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read: The Olympics have always been political In 2008, I attended the Beijing Olympics as a member of WADA's independent-observer team.\", \"from\": 3256, \"to\": 3392, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Olympics\", \"from\": 3262, \"to\": 3274}, {\"ngram\": \"the Beijing Olympics\", \"from\": 3322, \"to\": 3342}, {\"ngram\": \"a member\", \"from\": 3346, \"to\": 3354}, {\"ngram\": \"WADA's independent-observer team\", \"from\": 3358, \"to\": 3390}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As the newly appointed head of the United States Anti-Doping Agency, I was thrilled to be the WADA team's vice chair and legal expert, and eager to play my part in upholding the integrity of sports.\", \"from\": 3393, \"to\": 3591, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3428, \"end\": 3460, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"United States Anti-Doping Agency\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}, {\"begin\": 3428, \"end\": 3460, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"United States Anti-Doping Agency\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the newly appointed head\", \"from\": 3396, \"to\": 3420}, {\"ngram\": \"the WADA team's vice chair\", \"from\": 3483, \"to\": 3509}, {\"ngram\": \"legal expert\", \"from\": 3514, \"to\": 3526}, {\"ngram\": \"my part\", \"from\": 3546, \"to\": 3553}, {\"ngram\": \"the integrity\", \"from\": 3567, \"to\": 3580}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 3584, \"to\": 3590}]}, {\"sentence\": \"No doubt I was naive, but ever since that experience, aOne World, One Dreamframed picture from the Beijing Games has hung on my office wall.\", \"from\": 3592, \"to\": 3732, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that experience\", \"from\": 3629, \"to\": 3644}, {\"ngram\": \"aOne World\", \"from\": 3646, \"to\": 3656}, {\"ngram\": \"One Dreamframed picture\", \"from\": 3658, \"to\": 3681}, {\"ngram\": \"the Beijing Games\", \"from\": 3687, \"to\": 3704}, {\"ngram\": \"my office wall\", \"from\": 3717, \"to\": 3731}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Back then, my high hopes for doping-free sports did not seem so naive.\", \"from\": 3734, \"to\": 3804, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my high hopes\", \"from\": 3745, \"to\": 3758}, {\"ngram\": \"doping-free sports\", \"from\": 3763, \"to\": 3781}]}, {\"sentence\": \"During Jacques Rogge's tenure as the president of the International Olympic Committee, WADA was at the peak of its prowessin makingthe Olympics free from cheating.\", \"from\": 3805, \"to\": 3968, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3812, \"end\": 3825, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jacques_Rogge\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jacques Rogge\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q30461\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jacques_Rogge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jacques_Rogge\"}, {\"begin\": 3859, \"end\": 3890, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the president\", \"from\": 3838, \"to\": 3851}, {\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 3892, \"to\": 3896}, {\"ngram\": \"the peak\", \"from\": 3904, \"to\": 3912}, {\"ngram\": \"its prowessin makingthe Olympics\", \"from\": 3916, \"to\": 3948}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As a medical doctor, Rogge understood the value of keeping sports both fair and healthy for the athletes taking part-with results and records that the public could believe in.\", \"from\": 3969, \"to\": 4144, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3990, \"end\": 3995, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jacques_Rogge\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rogge\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q30461\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jacques_Rogge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jacques_Rogge\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a medical doctor\", \"from\": 3972, \"to\": 3988}, {\"ngram\": \"the value\", \"from\": 4007, \"to\": 4016}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 4028, \"to\": 4034}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 4061, \"to\": 4073}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 4081, \"to\": 4085}, {\"ngram\": \"results\", \"from\": 4091, \"to\": 4098}, {\"ngram\": \"records\", \"from\": 4103, \"to\": 4110}, {\"ngram\": \"the public\", \"from\": 4116, \"to\": 4126}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And he found willing partners in WADA's leaders at the time, David Howman and John Fahey, who were determined to keep the anti-doping fight independent of politics.\", \"from\": 4145, \"to\": 4309, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"willing partners\", \"from\": 4158, \"to\": 4174}, {\"ngram\": \"WADA's leaders\", \"from\": 4178, \"to\": 4192}, {\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 4196, \"to\": 4204}, {\"ngram\": \"the anti-doping fight\", \"from\": 4263, \"to\": 4284}, {\"ngram\": \"politics\", \"from\": 4300, \"to\": 4308}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sadly, that has changed.\", \"from\": 4311, \"to\": 4335, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"These days, I find I very much need that reminder on my wall of the Games' sporting ideals.\", \"from\": 4336, \"to\": 4427, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that reminder\", \"from\": 4372, \"to\": 4385}, {\"ngram\": \"my wall\", \"from\": 4389, \"to\": 4396}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games' sporting ideals\", \"from\": 4400, \"to\": 4426}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Those ideals look tarnished now: The Olympic movement is rife with examples of sports hijacked for national and political purposes.\", \"from\": 4428, \"to\": 4559, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Those ideals\", \"from\": 4428, \"to\": 4440}, {\"ngram\": \"The Olympic movement\", \"from\": 4461, \"to\": 4481}, {\"ngram\": \"examples\", \"from\": 4495, \"to\": 4503}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 4507, \"to\": 4513}, {\"ngram\": \"national and political purposes\", \"from\": 4527, \"to\": 4558}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And the very agency charged with safeguarding clean competition, WADA, is implicated in the political theater.\", \"from\": 4560, \"to\": 4670, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the very agency\", \"from\": 4564, \"to\": 4579}, {\"ngram\": \"clean competition\", \"from\": 4606, \"to\": 4623}, {\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 4625, \"to\": 4629}, {\"ngram\": \"the political theater\", \"from\": 4648, \"to\": 4669}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The scandal involving China is only the latest instance of WADA's failure to uphold its mission.\", \"from\": 4672, \"to\": 4768, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4694, \"end\": 4699, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999999275232794, \"rank\": 7.212074791054842e-08, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The scandal\", \"from\": 4672, \"to\": 4683}, {\"ngram\": \"only the latest instance\", \"from\": 4703, \"to\": 4727}, {\"ngram\": \"WADA's failure\", \"from\": 4731, \"to\": 4745}, {\"ngram\": \"its mission\", \"from\": 4756, \"to\": 4767}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The erosion of its integrity and authority dates back to 2015, when Russia's manipulations leading up to the 2014 Winter Olympics in Sochi were exposed.\", \"from\": 4769, \"to\": 4921, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4837, \"end\": 4843, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.8989737752575124e-15, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 4902, \"end\": 4907, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2014_Winter_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.8343503555667172, \"rank\": 0.19853727313458372, \"text\": \"Sochi\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2014_Winter_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2014_Winter_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The erosion\", \"from\": 4769, \"to\": 4780}, {\"ngram\": \"its integrity\", \"from\": 4784, \"to\": 4797}, {\"ngram\": \"authority\", \"from\": 4802, \"to\": 4811}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2014 Winter Olympics\", \"from\": 4874, \"to\": 4898}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Those Games were tainted by a state-sponsored doping program that involved Moscow's apparatchiksinterfering with the testing protocolsto make adverse tests of its own doped athletes conveniently disappear from the system.\", \"from\": 4922, \"to\": 5143, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Those Games\", \"from\": 4922, \"to\": 4933}, {\"ngram\": \"a state-sponsored doping program\", \"from\": 4950, \"to\": 4982}, {\"ngram\": \"the testing protocolsto\", \"from\": 5035, \"to\": 5058}, {\"ngram\": \"adverse tests\", \"from\": 5064, \"to\": 5077}, {\"ngram\": \"its own doped athletes\", \"from\": 5081, \"to\": 5103}, {\"ngram\": \"the system\", \"from\": 5132, \"to\": 5142}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It became obvious that sports were being recruited as a tool of realpolitik when Russia's foreign minister complained about USADA's \\\"provocative anti-Russian demands\\\" to then-Secretary of State John Kerry, who upheld my agency's position that Russia had to comply with the WADA rules.\", \"from\": 5144, \"to\": 5428, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5225, \"end\": 5231, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.8989737752575124e-15, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 5268, \"end\": 5273, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USADA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}, {\"begin\": 5289, \"end\": 5301, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anti-Russian_sentiment\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"anti-Russian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anti-Russian_sentiment\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anti-Russian_sentiment\"}, {\"begin\": 5387, \"end\": 5393, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.8989737752575124e-15, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 5167, \"to\": 5173}, {\"ngram\": \"a tool\", \"from\": 5198, \"to\": 5204}, {\"ngram\": \"realpolitik\", \"from\": 5208, \"to\": 5219}, {\"ngram\": \"State\", \"from\": 5332, \"to\": 5337}, {\"ngram\": \"my agency's position\", \"from\": 5361, \"to\": 5381}, {\"ngram\": \"the WADA rules\", \"from\": 5413, \"to\": 5427}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From the May 2018 issue: The man who brought down Lance Armstrong The evidence of Russian cheating was irrefutable.\", \"from\": 5430, \"to\": 5546, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5480, \"end\": 5495, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lance_Armstrong\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.7885801316686906e-82, \"text\": \"Lance Armstrong\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lance_Armstrong\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lance_Armstrong\"}, {\"begin\": 5513, \"end\": 5520, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999999992969606, \"rank\": 4.836813576312048e-10, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the May 2018 issue\", \"from\": 5435, \"to\": 5453}, {\"ngram\": \"The evidence\", \"from\": 5496, \"to\": 5508}]}, {\"sentence\": \"My colleagues and I met with the whistleblowers, including the former director of Russia's testing laboratory, Grigory Rodchenkov, who had fled the country and sought asylum in America.\", \"from\": 5547, \"to\": 5732, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5629, \"end\": 5635, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.8989737752575124e-15, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 5658, \"end\": 5676, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grigory_Rodchenkov\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Grigory Rodchenkov\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grigory_Rodchenkov\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grigory_Rodchenkov\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"My colleagues\", \"from\": 5547, \"to\": 5560}, {\"ngram\": \"the whistleblowers\", \"from\": 5576, \"to\": 5594}, {\"ngram\": \"the former director\", \"from\": 5606, \"to\": 5625}, {\"ngram\": \"the country\", \"from\": 5691, \"to\": 5702}, {\"ngram\": \"asylum\", \"from\": 5714, \"to\": 5720}, {\"ngram\": \"America\", \"from\": 5724, \"to\": 5731}]}, {\"sentence\": \"USADA echoed the calls from several athlete groups-including WADA's own Athletes Committee, led by the Olympian Beckie Scott, and the IOC's equivalent committee under the leadership of another Olympian, Claudia Bokel-not to close the Russia investigation but to expand it.\", \"from\": 5733, \"to\": 6005, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5733, \"end\": 5738, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USADA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}, {\"begin\": 5836, \"end\": 5844, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.330349633792321e-20, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 5845, \"end\": 5857, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beckie_Scott\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Beckie Scott\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q4270517\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beckie_Scott\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beckie_Scott\"}, {\"begin\": 5867, \"end\": 5870, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.783139129312814e-66, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 5926, \"end\": 5934, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.330349633792321e-20, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 5936, \"end\": 5943, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Claudia_Blaisdel_Carrington\", \"score\": 0.9999999409310494, \"rank\": 5.906886030523597e-08, \"text\": \"Claudia\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Claudia_Blaisdel_Carrington\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Claudia_Blaisdel_Carrington\"}, {\"begin\": 5967, \"end\": 5987, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_interference_in_the_2016_United_States_elections\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.3280371794000453e-72, \"text\": \"Russia investigation\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_interference_in_the_2016_United_States_elections\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_interference_in_the_2016_United_States_elections\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the calls\", \"from\": 5746, \"to\": 5755}, {\"ngram\": \"several athlete groups\", \"from\": 5761, \"to\": 5783}, {\"ngram\": \"WADA's own Athletes Committee\", \"from\": 5794, \"to\": 5823}, {\"ngram\": \"the leadership\", \"from\": 5900, \"to\": 5914}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yet WADA, in anow-familiar pattern, refused to listen and declined to pursue the matter.\", \"from\": 6006, \"to\": 6094, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 6010, \"to\": 6014}, {\"ngram\": \"anow-familiar pattern\", \"from\": 6019, \"to\": 6040}, {\"ngram\": \"the matter\", \"from\": 6083, \"to\": 6093}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite my personal plea to the agency's director general in March 2016, WADA remained unmoved by the cries of clean athletes.\", \"from\": 6096, \"to\": 6222, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my personal plea\", \"from\": 6104, \"to\": 6120}, {\"ngram\": \"the agency's director general\", \"from\": 6124, \"to\": 6153}, {\"ngram\": \"March\", \"from\": 6157, \"to\": 6162}, {\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 6169, \"to\": 6173}, {\"ngram\": \"the cries\", \"from\": 6194, \"to\": 6203}, {\"ngram\": \"clean athletes\", \"from\": 6207, \"to\": 6221}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To be clear, these athletes make enormous sacrifices and undergo years of hard training to participate in Olympic competition.\", \"from\": 6223, \"to\": 6349, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these athletes\", \"from\": 6236, \"to\": 6250}, {\"ngram\": \"enormous sacrifices\", \"from\": 6256, \"to\": 6275}, {\"ngram\": \"years\", \"from\": 6288, \"to\": 6293}, {\"ngram\": \"hard training\", \"from\": 6297, \"to\": 6310}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic competition\", \"from\": 6329, \"to\": 6348}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But when anti-doping agencies fail, and even abet cheats, they make a mockery of the Olympic movement.\", \"from\": 6350, \"to\": 6452, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"anti-doping agencies\", \"from\": 6359, \"to\": 6379}, {\"ngram\": \"a mockery\", \"from\": 6418, \"to\": 6427}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic movement\", \"from\": 6431, \"to\": 6451}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The clean athletes' dreams are shattered by the greed and deception of those entrusted with safeguarding the purity of the Games.\", \"from\": 6453, \"to\": 6582, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The clean athletes' dreams\", \"from\": 6453, \"to\": 6479}, {\"ngram\": \"the greed\", \"from\": 6497, \"to\": 6506}, {\"ngram\": \"deception\", \"from\": 6511, \"to\": 6520}, {\"ngram\": \"the purity\", \"from\": 6558, \"to\": 6568}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 6572, \"to\": 6581}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the Sochi case, WADA's intransigence proved shortsighted.\", \"from\": 6584, \"to\": 6644, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6591, \"end\": 6596, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2014_Winter_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.8343503555667172, \"rank\": 0.19853727313458372, \"text\": \"Sochi\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2014_Winter_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2014_Winter_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"WADA's intransigence\", \"from\": 6603, \"to\": 6623}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Just weeks after my appeal to WADA, in May 2016,60 MinutesandThe New York Timesbroke the story-and forced the agency's hand,compelling action.\", \"from\": 6645, \"to\": 6787, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my appeal\", \"from\": 6662, \"to\": 6671}, {\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 6675, \"to\": 6679}, {\"ngram\": \"May 2016,60\", \"from\": 6684, \"to\": 6695}, {\"ngram\": \"the story\", \"from\": 6730, \"to\": 6739}, {\"ngram\": \"the agency's hand\", \"from\": 6751, \"to\": 6768}, {\"ngram\": \"compelling action\", \"from\": 6769, \"to\": 6786}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Congressheld hearingsabout WADA's failures, as it was entitled to do because American taxpayer dollars support the international anti-doping infrastructure.\", \"from\": 6788, \"to\": 6944, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6865, \"end\": 6873, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.455422135538356e-25, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Congressheld hearingsabout WADA's failures\", \"from\": 6788, \"to\": 6830}, {\"ngram\": \"the international anti-doping infrastructure\", \"from\": 6899, \"to\": 6943}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In fact, ironically enough, WADA succeeded in leveraging its own dereliction into an argument for more funding.\", \"from\": 6945, \"to\": 7056, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"fact\", \"from\": 6948, \"to\": 6952}, {\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 6973, \"to\": 6977}, {\"ngram\": \"its own dereliction\", \"from\": 7002, \"to\": 7021}, {\"ngram\": \"an argument\", \"from\": 7027, \"to\": 7038}, {\"ngram\": \"more funding\", \"from\": 7043, \"to\": 7055}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The agency made a pitch to its international backers that it needed new investigative powers, more personnel, and a 60 percent increase in its budget from 2018 through 2025.\", \"from\": 7058, \"to\": 7231, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The agency\", \"from\": 7058, \"to\": 7068}, {\"ngram\": \"a pitch\", \"from\": 7074, \"to\": 7081}, {\"ngram\": \"its international backers\", \"from\": 7085, \"to\": 7110}, {\"ngram\": \"new investigative powers\", \"from\": 7126, \"to\": 7150}, {\"ngram\": \"more personnel\", \"from\": 7152, \"to\": 7166}, {\"ngram\": \"a 60 percent increase\", \"from\": 7172, \"to\": 7193}, {\"ngram\": \"its budget\", \"from\": 7197, \"to\": 7207}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It got what it asked for, but the U.S. government also did its best to make WADA accountable.\", \"from\": 7232, \"to\": 7325, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7266, \"end\": 7270, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999989458956, \"rank\": 1.053868968342205e-09, \"text\": \"U.S.\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 7308, \"to\": 7312}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It insisted on a governing seat on the agency's board, and made U.S. funding of WADA no longer mandatory but discretionary.\", \"from\": 7326, \"to\": 7449, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a governing seat\", \"from\": 7341, \"to\": 7357}, {\"ngram\": \"the agency's board\", \"from\": 7361, \"to\": 7379}, {\"ngram\": \"U.S. funding\", \"from\": 7390, \"to\": 7402}, {\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 7406, \"to\": 7410}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read: A list of Russia's responses to the doping scandal In principle, WADA's job as global regulator is not complicated: All it has to do is apply the rules to the facts without fear or favor.\", \"from\": 7451, \"to\": 7645, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7467, \"end\": 7473, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.8989737752575124e-15, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Read\", \"from\": 7451, \"to\": 7455}, {\"ngram\": \"A list\", \"from\": 7457, \"to\": 7463}, {\"ngram\": \"the doping scandal\", \"from\": 7489, \"to\": 7507}, {\"ngram\": \"principle\", \"from\": 7511, \"to\": 7520}, {\"ngram\": \"WADA's job\", \"from\": 7522, \"to\": 7532}, {\"ngram\": \"global regulator\", \"from\": 7536, \"to\": 7552}, {\"ngram\": \"the rules\", \"from\": 7599, \"to\": 7608}, {\"ngram\": \"the facts\", \"from\": 7612, \"to\": 7621}, {\"ngram\": \"fear\", \"from\": 7630, \"to\": 7634}, {\"ngram\": \"favor\", \"from\": 7638, \"to\": 7643}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the pursuit of global power-politics in sports is a systemic problem that overrules any notion of fair play, and WADA failed to deploy its new tools effectively.\", \"from\": 7646, \"to\": 7811, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the pursuit\", \"from\": 7650, \"to\": 7661}, {\"ngram\": \"global power-politics\", \"from\": 7665, \"to\": 7686}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 7690, \"to\": 7696}, {\"ngram\": \"a systemic problem\", \"from\": 7700, \"to\": 7718}, {\"ngram\": \"any notion\", \"from\": 7734, \"to\": 7744}, {\"ngram\": \"fair play\", \"from\": 7748, \"to\": 7757}, {\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 7763, \"to\": 7767}, {\"ngram\": \"its new tools\", \"from\": 7785, \"to\": 7798}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When WADAreceived noticeof the Chinese swimmers' positives in 2021, it should have sanctioned CHINADA for its mishandling of the violations.\", \"from\": 7812, \"to\": 7952, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7843, \"end\": 7850, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999999994251993, \"rank\": 5.749223433152553e-10, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"CHINADA\", \"from\": 7906, \"to\": 7913}, {\"ngram\": \"its mishandling\", \"from\": 7918, \"to\": 7933}, {\"ngram\": \"the violations\", \"from\": 7937, \"to\": 7951}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The postive-test findings occurred just months, in fact, before Beijing was to host the 2022 Winter Olympics.\", \"from\": 7954, \"to\": 8063, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8018, \"end\": 8025, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_China\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.26005679474013e-16, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The postive-test findings\", \"from\": 7954, \"to\": 7979}, {\"ngram\": \"fact\", \"from\": 8005, \"to\": 8009}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2022 Winter Olympics\", \"from\": 8038, \"to\": 8062}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So had WADA applied the rules correctly, both China and the IOC itself would have faced grave embarrassment.\", \"from\": 8064, \"to\": 8172, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8110, \"end\": 8115, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999999275232794, \"rank\": 7.212074791054842e-08, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 8124, \"end\": 8127, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.783139129312814e-66, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 8071, \"to\": 8075}, {\"ngram\": \"the rules\", \"from\": 8084, \"to\": 8093}, {\"ngram\": \"grave embarrassment\", \"from\": 8152, \"to\": 8171}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, WADA chose to give one country-a very powerful, rising country that had already been favored as host of the next Games-preferential treatment.\", \"from\": 8173, \"to\": 8324, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 8182, \"to\": 8186}, {\"ngram\": \"one country\", \"from\": 8201, \"to\": 8212}, {\"ngram\": \"a very powerful, rising country\", \"from\": 8213, \"to\": 8244}, {\"ngram\": \"host\", \"from\": 8278, \"to\": 8282}, {\"ngram\": \"the next Games-preferential treatment\", \"from\": 8286, \"to\": 8323}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Do we think for a second that WADA would have overlooked the burying of these tests if they had come from a small, poor country in Africa or South America instead of China?\", \"from\": 8325, \"to\": 8497, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8491, \"end\": 8496, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999999275232794, \"rank\": 7.212074791054842e-08, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a second\", \"from\": 8341, \"to\": 8349}, {\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 8355, \"to\": 8359}, {\"ngram\": \"the burying\", \"from\": 8382, \"to\": 8393}, {\"ngram\": \"these tests\", \"from\": 8397, \"to\": 8408}, {\"ngram\": \"a small, poor country\", \"from\": 8431, \"to\": 8452}, {\"ngram\": \"Africa\", \"from\": 8456, \"to\": 8462}, {\"ngram\": \"South America\", \"from\": 8466, \"to\": 8479}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2019 and 2020, WADAreceived almost $2 millionfrom the Chinese governmentabovethat country's required dues to the agency.\", \"from\": 8499, \"to\": 8622, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8556, \"end\": 8563, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999999994251993, \"rank\": 5.749223433152553e-10, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the agency\", \"from\": 8611, \"to\": 8621}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Then, in early 2023, WADA signed an undisclosedsponsorship agreementwith the largest sporting-goods manufacturer in China, Anta-a company that also has a sponsorship deal with the Chinese Swimming Federation.\", \"from\": 8623, \"to\": 8831, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8739, \"end\": 8744, \"